The paper deals with active learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The problem is specifically studied on trees and graphs, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the subcategories of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DM). The use of a mincut classifier and the optimization of the trade-off between number of queries and number of mistakes on non-queried nodes suggest that the paper could also belong to the subcategories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
